        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Tyler Clementi Higher Education Anti-Harassment Act of 2021</b></p> <p>This bill addresses harassment at institutions of higher education (IHEs).</p> <p> Specifically, the bill requires each IHE to include in its annual security report a statement of policy regarding harassment on the basis of a student's actual or perceived race, color, national origin, sex (including sexual orientation, gender identity, pregnancy, childbirth, a medical condition related to pregnancy or childbirth, and a sex stereotype), disability, or religion.</p> <p>In addition, the Department of Education may award grants to IHEs to initiate, expand, or improve programs to (1) prevent the harassment of students; (2) provide counseling or redress services to students who have been harassed or accused of subjecting other students to harassment; or (3) educate and train students, faculty, or staff to prevent harassment or address harassment if it occurs.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
